steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"2qtet","text":"Add Trypsin (5 ml for 15-cm plate) and incubate for     (37°C; 5% CO2)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":53,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"468ck","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"","data":{"duration":300,"guid":"65EDD2E07D6011ECB0AEC528C800364D","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8bd6c","text":"Add 10 ml MEF medium to neutralize the Trypsin and collect the solution into a conical tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5pgkd","text":"Discard supernatant, and re-suspend the cells in MEF Freezing Medium I at a concentration 2X the desired final freezing concentration (Freezing concentration will vary with MEF usage.)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3kgr2","text":"While swirling, slowly and drop-wise, add an equal volume of MEF Freezing Medium II to the cell suspension.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c8t1k","text":"Dispense cell mixture into pre-labeled cryovials (10x106) including type of cells, passage number, date frozen, and who handled cells.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":55,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"akthd","text":"Place cryovials into Styrofoam microtube freezer box or NALGENE™ Cryo 1°C Freezing Container pre-filled with 250 ml room temperature isopropanol.(This ensures that a -1°C/min rate of cooling is achieved, which is critical to cell viability.)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9nthi","text":"For long term storage, store cryovials in liquid nitrogen (-196ºC).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
